                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12697945" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2009 20:37:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1424&quot; title=&quot;Change all multi-term querys so that they extend MultiTermQuery and allow for a constant score mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-1424&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1424&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and 1425 committed, I think this is now possible with Solr. It will only work with the Phrase Highlighter, but thats probably the highlighter you should be using anyway (highlighting phrases properly is nice and expected, and its not any slower for non phrase highlighting).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Still need a  patch and a Lucene jar upgrade though. I will be happy to see highlightable wildcard/range queries again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12703472" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 Apr 2009 02:24:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve worked out most of this, but there is an issue that I have to fix in the Lucene highlighter first, so its this will have to wait for that (working on it) and &lt;b&gt;another&lt;/b&gt; Lucene jar update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705338" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sat, 2 May 2009 23:49:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Still needs some tests and a Lucene highlighter jar update, but this will do it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12705344" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 3 May 2009 00:27:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;a little null pointer fix and a couple tests from Hoss in one of the related issues (with a new arg to enforce multi term expanding with the span highlighter)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775560" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:51:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
